125 "§33-5-14
126 (a) The description of the vessel of a manufacturer or
127 dealer shall be omitted from the certificate of registration
128 since the number awarded may be used on different vessels at
129 different times. In lieu of the vessel's description, the word
130 "manufacturer" or "dealer," as appropriate, shall be plainly
131 marked on each certificate of registration.
132 (b) The manufacturer or dealer may have the number
133 awarded printed upon or attached to a removable sign or signs
134 to be temporarily but firmly mounted upon or attached to the
135 vessel being demonstrated or tested so long asif the display
136 meets the requirements of this article.
137 (c) A certificate of registration and the corresponding
138 number issued pursuant to this section may only be used for
139 vessels being demonstrated or tested."
